ow if thin/short.","why_useful":"what the market is saying about the stock \u2014 trend, leadership vs the index/sector, and tradeability.","why_it_can_fail":"corporate-action gaps, illiquid names, or a short listing history can distort returns/DMA/RS."}},"business":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"flags":[{"label":"Business quality","value":66.7,"unit":"/100","status":"ok","read":"Average quality (67/100).","meaning":"Composite of profitability, return on capital, balance-sheet safety and cash conversion (the Fundamentals-tab Quality score).","why_useful":"A durable, high-return business compounds value; a low-quality one needs a bigger margin of safety.","why_it_can_fail":"A single composite can mask a weak component; open the Fundamentals tab for the breakdown."},{"label":"Cash conversion","value":13.1,"unit":"\u00d7","status":"good","read":"13.10\u00d7 of profit came in as operating cash (5-yr median) \u2014 well backed.","meaning":"Median of (cash from operations \u00f7 net profit) over the last 5 years.","why_useful":"Profit you can't collect as cash is fragile; >0.8\u00d7 means earnings are real cash, <0.6\u00d7 is an accrual red flag.","why_it_can_fail":"One-off working-capital swings or a capex year can distort a single ratio; the 5-yr median smooths it."},{"label":"Balance-sheet safety","value":2.14,"unit":"\u00d7 D/E","status":"weak","read":"Leveraged (D/E 2.14\u00d7, interest cover 1.5\u00d7).","meaning":"Latest debt-to-equity and interest coverage (EBIT \u00f7 interest) from the balance sheet.","why_useful":"Low debt and high interest cover let a business survive a downturn; high debt amplifies trouble.","why_it_can_fail":"Off-balance-sheet leases/guarantees aren't captured; a cash-rich firm can show low D/E yet still be risky elsewhere."},{"label":"Earnings momentum","value":175.81,"unit":"% YoY","status":"good","read":"Profit up 176% YoY (latest TTM).","meaning":"Trailing-twelve-month net profit vs the year-ago TTM (and whether the YoY rate is rising = 'accelerating').","why_useful":"Improving, accelerating earnings tend to drive re-rating; falling profit warns of a deteriorating business.","why_it_can_fail":"TTM can be lumpy for cyclicals/one-offs; cross-check the multi-year trend on the Fundamentals tab."}]},"valuation":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"pe_now":56.8,"pe_percentile":6.0,"median_pe":59.3,"earnings_yield_pct":1.76,"pb":8.4,"ev_ebitda":11.08,"quality_score":67.0,"pat_cagr_5y_pct":null,"peg":null,"cheapness":{"status":"good","read":"P/E at the 6-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 cheap vs its own history."},"expectations":"Trades at 56.8\u00d7 earnings; multi-year growth not estimable, so 'priced-in' growth is unclear.","cyclical_caveat":null,"meaning":"P/E percentile = where today's price-to-earnings sits within the stock's own last-10-yr range (low = cheap vs its past). Paired with the Quality score and 5-yr profit growth so a cheap multiple is judged against business strength, not in isolation.","why_useful":"Cheapness only matters relative to quality and growth \u2014 a low P/E on a declining or peak-cyclical business is a trap, not a bargain.","why_it_can_fail":"P/E breaks for loss-makers / one-offs; for banks use P/B not EV/EBITDA; a multiple cheap vs history can stay cheap if the business has structurally de-rated."},"ownership":{"ok":true,"na":null,"holders":{"Promoter":{"periods":["Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[46.58,46.6,46.6,46.6],"latest_pct":46.6,"chg_1y_pp":0.02},"FII":{"periods":["Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[22.59,21.59,16.25,12.78],"latest_pct":12.78,"chg_1y_pp":-9.81},"DII":{"periods":["Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[10.96,11.48,17.05,20.24],"latest_pct":20.24,"chg_1y_pp":9.28},"Public":{"periods":["Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[19.51,19.98,19.58,19.87],"latest_pct":19.87,"chg_1y_pp":0.36}},"pledge":null,"events":[],"placeholders":[{"label":"Promoter pledge (detail)","note":"share-level pledge history \u2014 fetchable via NSE, deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Bulk / block deals","note":"large on-market trades \u2014 NSE feed, deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Insider / SAST disclosures","note":"promoter & designated-person dealings \u2014 deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Exchange announcements","note":"NSE/BSE filings stream \u2014 deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Results calendar","note":"next board-meeting / results date \u2014 deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Credit ratings","note":"rating-agency actions \u2014 deferred to MVP-2."}],"reads":{"Promoter":"Promoter stake up 0.02pp over ~1yr \u2192 46.60%.","FII":"FIIs reducing (-9.81pp YoY \u2192 12.78%).","DII":"DIIs adding (+9.28pp YoY \u2192 20.24%)."},"meaning":"Quarterly shareholding (% held by Promoters / Foreign (FII) / Domestic (DII) institutions / Public) from Screener, plus exchange corporate actions tagged by materiality (High = structural: bonus/split/buyback/merger; Low = routine: dividend/AGM).","why_useful":"Rising promoter & institutional ownership and clean corporate actions are confirming signals; falling promoter stake or pledging is a governance/skin-in-the-game warning.","why_it_can_fail":"Shareholding is a lagged quarterly snapshot; promoter % can fall for benign reasons (QIP, ESOP dilution). Pledge & insider detail are deferred (placeholders below)."},"snapshot":{"dimensions":{"Market":{"verdict":"negative","score":-3,"drivers":["\u2212 Below its 200-day average (-17%) \u2014 downtrend.","\u00b7 50-day average still below the 200-day (no golden cross).","\u2212 41% below its 52-week high.","\u2212 In a deep drawdown (-41% from its peak)."],"rule":"Points: +1 price above its 200-day average \u00b7 +1 a golden cross (50-day \u2265 200-day) \u00b7 +1 within 10% of the 52-week high \u00b7 +1 beating the NIFTY 500 over 12 months; \u22121 for each opposite, and \u22121 if more than 25% below its peak. Verdict: positive at +2 or more, negative at \u22122 or less, otherwise neutral."},"Business":{"verdict":"neutral","score":1,"drivers":["\u00b7 Average quality (67/100).","+ 13.10\u00d7 of profit came in as operating cash (5-yr median) \u2014 well backed.","\u2212 Leveraged (D/E 2.14\u00d7, interest cover 1.5\u00d7).","+ Profit up 176% YoY (latest TTM)."],"rule":"Points across the four business flags: +1 for each that is 'good' (quality, cash conversion, balance-sheet safety, earnings momentum), \u22121 for each that is 'weak'. Verdict: positive at +2 or more, negative at \u22122 or less."},"Valuation":{"verdict":"positive","score":2,"drivers":["+ P/E at the 6-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 cheap vs its own history."],"rule":"Cheap \u2014 P/E below the 30th percentile of its own 10-year range \u2014 scores +2 (supportive); expensive (above the 70th) scores \u22122; mid-range is 0. A peak/cyclical-earnings flag discounts a cheap read to +1. NOTE: 'positive' means the multiple looks supportive vs the stock's OWN history \u2014 it is NOT a buy call."},"Ownership":{"verdict":"positive","score":2,"drivers":["+ Promoter stake rising (+0.02pp YoY).","+ DIIs accumulating (+9.28pp YoY)."],"rule":"Points: +1 promoter stake rising \u00b7 \u22121 promoter stake falling more than 1pp in a year \u00b7 \u22121 promoter pledge above 10% \u00b7 +1 for each of FII / DII accumulating (>0.5pp in a year). Verdict: positive at +1 or more, negative at \u22121 or less."}},"top_positives":["13.10\u00d7 of profit came in as operating cash (5-yr median) \u2014 well backed.","Profit up 176% YoY (latest TTM).","P/E at the 6-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 cheap vs its own history.","Promoter stake rising (+0.02pp YoY).","DIIs accumulating (+9.28pp YoY)."],"key_risks":["Below its 200-day average (-17%) \u2014 downtrend.","41% below its 52-week high.","In a deep drawdown (-41% from its peak).","Leveraged (D/E 2.14\u00d7, interest cover 1.5\u00d7)."],"monitor_next":["Next quarterly results (board-meeting date is an MVP-2 placeholder).","Re-rating toward / away from its median P/E (59.